# midiin: polyphonic allocation (manual "Polyphonic patches", lines 58-79).
# Three voices, roundrobin default 0 (search always starts at pitch1, line 339)
# and voiceallocation default 0 (steal the OLDEST note when all voices busy,
# line 340). Notes 60/64/67 fill voices 1/2/3 lowest-first. A fourth note (72)
# with all voices busy steals voice 1 (oldest). Then releasing note 64 frees
# only voice 2.
patch <<<
[midiin]
    pitch1 = O1
    pitch2 = O2
    pitch3 = O3
    gate1  = O4
    gate2  = O5
    gate3  = O6
>>>
@0 midisend trs noteon 1 60 100
@0 expect O1 0.3
@0 expect O4 1
@1 midisend trs noteon 1 64 100
@1 expect O2 0.333333 tol 0.0001
@1 expect O5 1
@2 midisend trs noteon 1 67 100
@2 expect O3 0.358333 tol 0.0001
@2 expect O6 1
@3 midisend trs noteon 1 72 100
@3 expect O1 0.4
@3 expect O4 1
@4 midisend trs noteoff 1 64 0
@4 expect O5 0
@4 expect O4 1
@4 expect O6 1
